  <section class="row section styleguide-section with-copy">
    <h2 id="interaction">Interaction</h2>
    <p>Neue includes some helper scripts for interactivity. While any application-specific logic should live within its own codebase, you can find the logic that powers some of our reusable patterns here:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/docs/jump-scroll.html">jump-scroll.js</a>: Applies a smooth-scroll animation on links with the <code>.js-jumpscroll</code> class.</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/scroll-indicator.html">scroll-indicator.js</a>: Indicates current section in nav on scroll.</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/menu.html">menu.js</a>: Initializes site-wide menu chrome functionality.</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/modal.html">modal.js</a>: Show/hide modals.</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/sticky.html">sticky.js</a>: Pins an element to the top of the screen on scroll.</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/validation.html">validation.js</a>: Client-side form validation logic.</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/ValidationFunctions.html">ValidationFunctions.js</a>: Individual validation checks (name, email, etc.)</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/carousel.html">carousel.js</a>: Carousel (image gallery) behavior.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

